# Sprite Workbench Design System Rules

This project is a browser-based game development toolchain with a hand-crafted dark-theme design system. **No framework, no build step, no Tailwind.** Pure HTML/CSS/JS.

The canonical style guide is at `STYLE_GUIDE.md` in the project root. Read it before any frontend work.

---

## Color Rules

**ONLY use these CSS custom properties. Never hardcode hex values.**

```css
/* Backgrounds */
var(--bg)         /* #050709  — page background */
var(--panel)      /* rgba(4,6,10,0.96) — panel surfaces */
var(--panel-soft) /* #07090c — secondary panel */

/* Accent (cyan — active/selected/focused states ONLY) */
var(--accent)      /* #00e8c8 */
var(--accent-soft) /* rgba(0,232,200,0.08) */

/* Text */
var(--text)   /* #cce8e0 — primary */
var(--muted)  /* #5d7870 — secondary/labels */

/* Borders */
var(--stroke)        /* rgba(0,232,200,0.07) — default panel border */
var(--stroke-strong) /* rgba(0,232,200,0.14) */
var(--line)          /* rgba(0,232,200,0.10) — dividers */
var(--line-strong)   /* rgba(0,232,200,0.18) */

/* Semantic */
var(--good)         /* #4ade80 — success */
var(--good-soft)    /* rgba(74,222,128,0.12) */
var(--warning)      /* #d29922 — caution */
var(--warning-soft) /* rgba(210,153,34,0.16) */
var(--error)        /* #f85149 — error/destructive */
var(--error-soft)   /* rgba(248,81,73,0.16) */
```

**Gold (primary CTA only):**
```css
background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(245,208,116,0.92), rgba(220,176,73,0.92));
color: #16120a;
```

